  <div>

    <div class="dxpnlControl_MaterialCompact" id="cbpAnnouncements">
      <p>
        <font style="font:bold;font-size:24px">Informational: Description box update</font> posted on 3/10/2026
      </p>Test<br>
      <br><i>Effective as of 3/9/2026</i>
      <hr>
      <p>
        <font style="font:bold;font-size:24px">Portal Enhancements: Bulk E-Signature Verification Requests and Reminders
        </font> posted on 2/20/2026
      </p>
      <div style="font-family: inherit; line-height: 1.6; color: #222; max-width: 800px;">



        <ul style="margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 16px;">

          <li>

            You can find an updated <strong>User Guide</strong> on the Portal Documents tab.

          </li>

          <li style="margin-top: 4px;">

            <strong>To ensure you are seeing the latest version of the portal,</strong> you may need to perform a hard
            refresh.<br>

            <em>Windows:</em> Press <code>Ctrl</code> + <code>Shift</code> + <code>R</code> OR <code>Ctrl</code> +
            <code>F5</code>

            <em>Mac:</em> Press <code>Cmd</code> + <code>Shift</code> + <code>R</code>.

          </li>

        </ul>







        <p style="color: #003057; font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-top: 14px; margin-bottom: 4px;"> Bulk
          E-Signature Verification Requests </p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 6px;">

          You can now send E-Signature Verification Requests to up to 500 plaintiffs at once using the Bulk Actions tab.
          Only plaintiffs with no outstanding items will be eligible for bulk signature. Please refer to Section V.
          Adding a Plaintiff to the Portal – G. Completing a Verification (page 23) in the User Guide </p>





        <p style="color: #003057; font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-top: 14px; margin-bottom: 4px;"> Reminders
        </p>



        <ul style="margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 16px;">

          <li>Documents can be uploaded in bulk regardless of Plaintiff status.

          </li>



          <li> SDWIS IDs can be updated via Import

          </li>





        </ul>
      </div> <br>
      <hr>
      <p>
        <font style="font:bold;font-size:24px">Reminders: test</font> posted on 11/14/2025
      </p>
      <div style="font-family: inherit; line-height: 1.6; color: #222; max-width: 800px;">

        <h2 style="color: red; font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; text-transform: uppercase;">
          Important Maintenance Notice
        </h2>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
          The AFFF MDL Portal will offline for scheduled maintenance beginning <strong>Friday, November 14th at 5:00 pm
            CST</strong>. The portal will be back online no later than Monday, November 17th at 8:00 am CST. We will
          post an announcement once maintenance is complete and the portal is accessible.
        </p>

      </div>
      <br>
      <hr>
      <p>
        <font style="font:bold;font-size:24px">Reminders: test</font> posted on 11/11/2025
      </p>
      <div style="font-family: inherit; line-height: 1.6; color: #222; max-width: 800px;">

        <p style="font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
          Updates were rolled out to the portal today.
        </p>

        <ul style="margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 16px;">
          <li>
            You can find an updated <strong>User Guide</strong> on the Portal Documents tab.
          </li>
          <li style="margin-top: 4px;">
            <strong>To ensure you are seeing the latest version of the portal,</strong> you may need to perform a hard
            refresh.<br>
            <em>Windows:</em> Press <code>Ctrl</code> + <code>Shift</code> + <code>R</code> OR <code>Ctrl</code> +
            <code>F5</code>
            <em>Mac:</em> Press <code>Cmd</code> + <code>Shift</code> + <code>R</code>.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p style="color: #003057; font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-top: 14px; margin-bottom: 4px;">Electronic
          Verification</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
          The system will now default to sending the signature request to the email address listed on the Plaintiff
          Information tab. An alternative signer email may be provided if necessary. </p>


        <p style="color: #003057; font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-top: 14px; margin-bottom: 4px;">Expert
          Disclosure</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
          This question will no longer be required for submission to accommodate varying requirements. </p>

        <p style="color: #003057; font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-top: 14px; margin-bottom: 4px;">Plaintiff
          Enrollment Report</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
          Additional fields are now available on this report that were already stored on the Plaintiff Information tab
          such as plaintiff address, plaintiff email address, and original filing information. </p>

        <p style="color: #003057; font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-top: 14px; margin-bottom: 4px;">Incomplete
          Items Report </p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 4px;">
          A new report is now available that lists all incomplete items required for submission for each plaintiff. The
          report includes a full description of each incomplete item.
        </p>

      </div>
      <br>
      <br><i>Effective as of 1/1/2025</i>
      <hr>
